data.text: Number 52A 1SupplementPublished by AuthorityFRIDAY, 29th JUNE, 2007This publication is registered for transmission by Inland Post as a newspaper. The postage rate to places within Ireland (32 counties), places in Britain and otherplaces the printed paper rate by weight applies.SEANAD ELECTORAL (PANEL MEMBERS) ACTS 1947 AND 1954ELECTORAL ROLLThe Electoral Roll prepared by the Seanad Returning Officer under section 45 of the Seanad Electoral (Panel Members) Act 1947, asamended by the Seanad Electoral (Panel Members) Act 1954, of persons entitled under section 44 of the Act of 1947 to vote at the election ofpanel members at the Seanad General Election consequent on the dissolution of Dáil Éireann by the Proclamation of the President of the 29thday of April, 2007.Under the heading ‘‘Description’’ the Letter D denotes ‘‘a member of Dáil Éireann’’.,, ,, ,, ,, ,, ,, S ,, ‘‘a member of Seanad Éireann’’.,, ,, ,, ,, ,, ,, L ,, ‘‘a member of the council of a county or city’’.Uimh.
